		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://andyweigel.com/client/cwa-main/?p=877</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>Charles Wright Academy is proud to host Steve &#38; Kate&#8217;s Camp on our Tacoma campus for the fourth summer! Running Monday through Friday (7:30 a.m. to 6 p.m.) from June 15 through August 28, this year&#8217;s camp is open to pre-kindergartners up to seventh graders. Founded in 1980, Steve &#38; Kate&#8217;s Camp conforms to kids—not [&#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.charleswright.org/steve-kates-camp-2015/">Steve &#038; Kate&#8217;s Camp 2015</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.charleswright.org">Charles Wright Academy</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Charles Wright Academy is proud to host Steve &amp; Kate&#8217;s Camp on our Tacoma campus for the fourth summer! Running Monday through Friday (7:30 a.m. to 6 p.m.) from June 15 through August 28, this year&#8217;s camp is open to pre-kindergartners up to seventh graders.</p>
<p>Founded in 1980, Steve &amp; Kate&#8217;s Camp conforms to kids—not the other way around. Instead of a rigid structure, Steve &amp; Kate&#8217;s gives their summer campers a choice. Instead of teaching kids the typical way, they give them tools and gentle guidance to help them become autodidacts (people who teach themselves). The difference is subtle—and it’s profound. There are a gazillion ways for kids to design a day at Steve &amp; Kate&#8217;s Camp. One camper might dive into breadmaking and animation while another flies down a water slide and scores a goal in our inflatable soccer stadium. It’s up to them. Studio options this year include the Animation Studio, the Breadmaking Studio, the Dance Studio, the Music Studio, the Style Studio, and the brand-new Coding Studio.</p>
<p>Steve &amp; Kate&#8217;s Camp gives parents flexibility, too! Their plans are designed to grant peace of mind like Raja yoga. You can buy any number of day passes, use them whenever you want, and get an automatic refund for unused passes. If you need the whole summer, they’ve got a membership, too. You don’t even need to tell them when you’re coming. Lunch and materials are included. Now peace of mind can be attained without having to get into a downward dog pose. Namaste.</p>
<p>Visit here for more information about registration.</p>
<p><strong>Date:</strong><br />
06/15/2015-08/28/2015</p>
<p><strong>Location:</strong><br />
Charles Wright Academy</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.charleswright.org/steve-kates-camp-2015/">Steve &#038; Kate&#8217;s Camp 2015</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.charleswright.org">Charles Wright Academy</a>.</p>
